Subject: Re: [T2] solenoid and starter check

Sounds like you are on the right track - be sure you don't get run over by 
the vehicle when you bridge the terminals on the starter.

Somebody posted an article where a bus owner did just that!!!

Helper, bus in neutral, foot on brake, foot on clutch.

>So my 71 westy decided to not start yesterday, so I push started it and it 
>drove home just fine, but this morning it just clicks when I turn it over 
>so I thought I would check the solenoid and starter today but wanted to 
>make sure I do it right. so.....
>1. Check all wires and contacts
>2. ignition off, bus in neutral screwdriver across the 2 large contacts on 
>the solenoid?  It whirls then starter is ok? If not starter is problem?
>3. Screwdriver between battery contact on solenoid and to terminal to 
>ignition?  It whirls then solenoid is bad?

